body:
There's a couple of failures. I haven't look too deeply, is this just a concurrent change or is this a difference to Py2 (maybe preferring more local classes in superclass lists?):

```
  path: "tensorflow.train.MonitoredSession.StepContext"
  tf_class {
-   is_instance: "<class \'google3.third_party.tensorflow.python.training.monitored_session.StepContext\'>"
+   is_instance: "<class \'google3.third_party.tensorflow.python.training.monitored_session._MonitoredSession.StepContext\'>"
```

and 

```
  path: "tensorflow.train.SingularMonitoredSession.StepContext"
  tf_class {
-   is_instance: "<class \'google3.third_party.tensorflow.python.training.monitored_session.StepContext\'>"
+   is_instance: "<class \'google3.third_party.tensorflow.python.training.monitored_session._MonitoredSession.StepContext\'>"
```

and

```
  path: "tensorflow.Variable.SaveSliceInfo"
  tf_class {
-   is_instance: "<class \'google3.third_party.tensorflow.python.ops.variables.SaveSliceInfo\'>"
+   is_instance: "<class \'google3.third_party.tensorflow.python.ops.variables.Variable.SaveSliceInfo\'>"
```
